inn1.comm: a slower ball to start with, I think. Strauss seemed to have so much time on the back foot, and was a little early on it
forced off the back foot behind square on the off side
wide of the off stump, too wide
late on this square cut, Strauss's bread and butter - this pitch is dog slow. Goes for his favoured cut and inside edges it
wide of the off stump, and this one carries through nicely
excellent delivery at 90.7mph just outside off, cramping Strauss for room, and the added bounce further restricts his forcing shot off the back foot as Lee completes a tidy maiden
short of a length and tucked around the corner. A quiet crowd cheer with English irony as England, and Bopara, are off the mark at last
again a bit too short and left alone
a good one from the alice-band-wearing left-arm pacer which cuts away from Strauss's little waft outside off
flashed to point off the back foot
firmly worked from the off stump to mid-on
short of a length and tucked to leg
thick outside edge which flies to third man! Perfectly safe edge all along the ground
oh he's timed that nicely. Quickly onto the pull, which he did sky and spoon a little, but it was perfectly safe and landed a foot inside the rope for four
thwackingly good stroke. On the front foot this time, and he slams it through cover. Too full from Lee
poor ball, right in Strauss's slot. It's cut with serious hammer for four. Top batting
left alone this time outside off
on the off stump and punched back to Lee. Handbags! Rompingly pink handbags at dawn as Lee threatens to knock Strauss's head off, before they both smile and chuckle and enjoy the crowd's jeers
flicked to leg
nearly! Weak, nothing sort of stroke by Bopara as he came forward and got an inside edge onto his pads
on the back foot, he defends
wide of the off stump and left alone

punched out to mid-off and they'll have to be quick - the throw hits the stumps. Then Bopara goes for a second run, the monstrous winner that he is, and charges halfway down the pitch with Owais Shah-like awareness, but Strauss sends him back and the ball's wide anyway. Absolute total chaos
on the back foot, he defends
thick outside edge as Bopara goes for a drive, and Johnson mis-fields at third man just to check if the crowd still love him. They cheer and jeer his fumble, so that's affirmative
beaten with a cracker! That was seriously fast, holding its line just outside off and beating his outside edge
goes on the drive to mid-off
gives himself a bit of room and cuts it hard down to third man
short of a length, he cuts, he misses
impetuous but brilliant. Down the pitch from Bopara and he smashes this over long-on for six. That is a seriously good shot!
on the back foot, slower ball! Great stuff. Bopara's up to the mark and defends
nudged to leg this time
an orthodoxly solid drive to mid-off
driven out to the off side
onto the front foot and he blocks. Good comeback from Bracken after being boshed for six
oh he's timed that beautifully. Nothing more than a turn of the wrists but the pace of Lee, and his leg-stump line from around the wicket, sees that fly for four
very fast attempted yorker and Strauss steps to leg - but Lee follows him and tries to crush his toes
flicked to leg
on the front foot, he defends
and again he's timed that for four! Angling into his pads, and Strauss whipped it purposefully through midwicket for another boundary. He's playing a gem here, Strausss
on the back foot, gets into a bit of a tangle and isn't sure where the ball's gone
on the back foot, nudges to leg for a hasty single
fuller delivery and it's punched out to the off side
slower ball on middle-and-leg. Bopara's forward on the front foot
defended cautiously out to the off side
hammered off the back foot with Tendulkarish orthodoxy but straight to short extra-cover

brilliantly caught by Hopes! Bopara went for another impetuous crack over the top but got a leading, spiralling edge over the bowlers head and Hopes ran back a good eight or nine metres, taking the ball from over his head and diving in the process
left alone off the back foot. Good take from the keeper
on the back foot and nudged to mid-on
outside off and Prior flashes and misses! That climbed a lot on him, but it was a poor stroke indeed
on the back foot, he defends this on the back foot
short, he goes on the pull and pulls it straight to square leg! Johnson strikes! Another good, low catch by James Hopes and England's bright start has disappeared
mind your stumps, Owais. Steps back and nearly steps on them like he did in the last match
swings and misses! Excellent take by Paine who whips off the bails in hope. He's kept well this young keeper
forced off the back foot
short of a length and he goes for a pull, does so nicely
short of a length; he cuts and misses
cuts and misses once more!
Johnson runs in and fires a full ball outside off stump, Shah moves across and miss the drive
Shah moves across his stumps once again, he has to be careful here, he taps the ball into the vacant spaces at midwicket and runs the single, Shah wants the second but Strauss knows better
width offered outside off stump, Strauss cuts but finds the fielder
he hasn't found the fielder this time! Short, wide bowling and Strauss hammers it past Clarke at point, he really should have stopped that
Strauss goes for the cut again but doesn't make contact
short ball but it's misdirected down leg side, Johnson will have to rebowl that
better line and length from Johnson but Strauss waits on the back foot and dabs it late towards backward point, Shah is up for the quick single
Strauss wanted to hit that on the leg side but spliced it towards the off, it was full and straight from Hopes
Strauss goes on the back foot and muscles the ball towards square leg, it wasn't that short but he managed to pull it
played back to the bowler, gently
Shah strides forward and presents a straight bat while defending on the off side
played off the back foot towards point, tidy over this, one to go
Shah takes a step towards off and swats the ball, or tries to, towards leg, he doesn't time it well though
Johnson offers Strauss a delivery on his pads and he will be disappointed that he hasn't done more with it than play to fine leg for one, leg bye that too
Shah gets under one and sends it over cover, the ball bounces well before the rope and teases Callum Ferguson all the way to the boundary, Ferguson put in a spectacular dive but to no avail
short of a length on leg and middle, Shah jumps back and fends towards the leg side
strauss stays in his crease and nudges towards midwicket
straight ball from Johnson and Strauss whips off his pads behind square and calls Shah through for two
played towards point, England are 59 for 2
played carefully on the front foot towards the off side
Shah moves smoothly forward and blocks
width offered outside off and Shah cuts hard but places it wide enough of the third man fielder to come back for the second
played on the off but straight to the fielder
knocked off the pads towards midwicket, another dot
a bit too straight from Hopes but Shah misses the whip off the pads
that's too close to off stump for the cut, and Strauss missed it
good length and straight, Strauss opens the face ever so slightly and guides towards third man
Shah plants his front foot across his stumps and waits for the Johnson slower ball to reach him before defending
Shah sees width outside off and flays his bat at it, he doesn't connect with his mighty swing though

lbw! Shah moves across his stumps and tries to whip across the line through midwicket, he misses and gets hit on the pad, the umpire takes a good look and eventually raises the finger, replays show that the ball may have been missing off stump, Shah's a bit unlucky there, but it looks so close when he moves across his stumps like that
and he lets his first ball go through to the keeper
steady and straight from Hopes, defended on the back foot
nudged towards the leg side
fractionally short and Strauss latches on to it and pulls towards deep midwicket
Hopes pitches outside leg, allowing Strauss to flick off his pads towards deep square
short of a length and just outside off, Collingwood waits and lets ball hit bat

Hopes bowls a good length ball angling towards off and middle, Collingwood waits and just when you think it's too late, he thrusts his bat out and blocks it. Shouts of "OH!" from the Aussies but Colly was in control there
worked off his pads behind square for one
bah, short ball but down leg side, poor direction and that's a wide
short of a length outside off, Collingwood gets on top of the bounce and plays a crisp cut towards point, doesn't beat the fielder though
worked off the pads towards square leg
forced off the back foot but straight to the man at cover
fuller ball outside off, Collingwood leans into the drive and plays the ball to cover
full and straight from Johnson, Collingwood flicks the ball off his pad through midwicket
steady and straight again, played towards the leg side
Hopes slants the ball wide and draws Strauss into swishing at it, he swishes and misses
very similar shot but this time Strauss connects with the swish and runs the single
pushed off the back foot through cover point
Strauss pushes the ball off the front foot towards cover
Strauss leans across an drives the ball firmly and just wide of the fielder at mid-on, nicely placed
Strauss moves back and nudges towards short leg leg, Collingwood is off in a flash from the non-strikers end, that single brings up Strauss's fifty, well played but he needs to carry on
... and then blocks towards the off side
tossed up by Hauritz, it's a slow pitch this, Collingwood strides forward and blocks
he pulls out the slog sweep but the line is much too far outside off and Collingwood misses
worked off the front foot towards wide long on for one
Strauss waits on the back foot and works the ball behind square
Strauss swivels and pulls and will get two for his effort
fuller length and Strauss flicks from leg stump towards deep square
Collingwood swivels and tries to pull, he doesn't do it very well
oh! that just cleared the fielder, Collingwood chipped the ball in the air and it flew just over the fielder's head at midwicket, that was the offcutter from Hopes
Strauss stays in his crease and defends
Strauss stays in his crease again, rocks back and pulls the ball over wide mid-on, England end the Powerplay with a boundary
tossed up outside off and he cracks him to cover
down the leg side and tickled fine. That's top tickling, that
full and straight, Collingwood nudges (© P Collingwood)
Strauss forces this off the back foot
Strauss comes down the pitch, drives to long-on
chopped for nothing more than a single
driven back to Bracken who rather stiffly bends forward but can't pick it up. He looks like an arthritic giraffe sometimes
cheeky shot, plucking it out of Paine's gloves and down to third man. Ferguson cleans up
turned to leg
Collingwood stands tall. Collingwood cracks to cover. Collingwood stays where he is
angling into his pads (he's around the wicket, by the way), Collingwood works it to midwicket
short of a length and again flicked to deep square leg
good, flattish delivery but short enough to be pumped to mid-on
turned to leg
goddim! Down the pitch by Strauss, flicking it and timing it beautifully but it just carried to Michael Clarke, diving forward at short midwicket
tossed up on middle, he's forward and defending
smashed powerfully through cover
cuts back sharply on Strauss who chops out to the off side
very crisply struck, and he made a good stride forward there. Uses his feet really well, Morgan
forced off the back foot
good, straight delivery. He is a demon, Bracken, on surfaces like these. Hardly ever gets serious tap
forced off the back foot behind square
Collingwood drives firmly to mid-off. But, well, straight to mid-off
down the pitch, drives to mid-off
speared in fast on the off stump, Morgan drives
skips back, tries to give himself room but this is tremendous bowling from Hauritz, cramping him for room
stroked out nicely through extra cover
Collingwood swings and misses to a faster ball from The Ritzy
wider and well flighted, he strokes it tamely to mid-off
back-cut down to third man
late cut - nicely done, too. Good, soft hands
angling into the right-hander who defends. That was impossibly slow
punched forcefully off the back foot
outside off, forced to cover for another rip-roaring zero
another similar forcing shot, this time to mid-off.
quicker ball worked off his pads
shot! Reverse swept with great power for four. At last - some inventiveness from England, and he nailed it completely
skips down the pitch for a clunked single to long-off
whipped to leg
comes forward and pats a defensive
tries to work it to leg but can't...erm. Well, he just can't.
defended out to mid-off
full of length, driven out to cover
flicks this on the walk to the leg side
elegant little late dab out to the off side
another single to long-off
tossed up outside off, Morgan works him to long-on
stroked once more to long-off. Strokey
tossed up just outside off, he's forward and defending with solidity
short of a length and pushed off the back foot out to cover
good line but a bit too short and he guides it out to point
driven out to long-on
short and wide - is that four? No! Ah well. A single is almost as good, if 75% not as good. Firm cut finds deep cover point
starts with one just outside off to which he comes forward and drives, firmly
on the back foot, driven
slides into Collingwood's pads, and Watson roars an appeal but it's going down leg
flicked to square leg
on the front foot, Morgan blocks to cover
onto the front foot, he drives hard to mid-off
full ball with a hint of swing back into Collingwood, dug out by the batsman
full ball again, driven to mid-on for no run
Collingwood plays behind square and takes on the fielder, coming back for the second
Lee's right up there, 90mph full on middle stump, Collingwood stays where he is and blocks
Lee drags it short and wide, Collingwood dabs towards third man
full on off stump, driven towards mid off
Watson also gets the ball to swing into Collingwood, his footwork is tentative as he nudges towards midwicket, five men in the circle
there's a bit of width outside off stump and Collingwood is quick to cut towards deep point
Morgan forces the ball off is pads and hits it with enough power to get past midwicket
caught, Collingwood tries to hit down the ground but doesn't get enough elevation, he hits it straight to mid-on
he lets the fist ball go outside of stump
Watson swings the ball into the right-hander and Wright blocks on the front foot
goo length and straight from Lee, defended by the batsman
Wright moves forward and defends a full ball on the leg side
short ball but Lee's over-stepped, Wright ducks under the bouncer but has a free hit coming up
he clears his front foot out of the way and smashes the ball wide of the fielder at mid-off, powerful shot all the way for four
driven of the front foot towards mid off this time
Morgan moves forward and guides the ball past point for one more
short of a length outside of, played towards point where Clarke swoops on the ball and throws at the bowler's end, Morgan has to hurry back
wide of the off stump and he crashes and misses
on the back foot, he defends. Good, straight delivery
driven out to mid-off
short, he goes for a pull but misses. "Catttch" is the cry from what's his name, Watson
onto the front foot, he blocks
driven out to long-off
full ball outside off stump, Morgan strides forward and drives through cover
short of a length outside off stump, Wright whacks it but straight to Clarke at point
pushed off the back foot towards point
Wright stays in his crease and finds Clarke again at point
played off the back foot towards third man
short ball and Wright pulls towards deep square leg
Hopes bowls a cutter into the right-hander, Wright moves forward and defends, not very convincingly though
Wright plays the ball late and past the fielder at point for one
Hopes slants the ball across Morgan and he uses the angle to cut towards third man

there you go! Wright tries to blast the ball through cover but hits it hard and straight to Voges who takes a sharp low catch, England now don't have two specialist batsmen to utilise the final Powerplay
Bresnan gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends
Bresnan eases on to the front foot and pushes the ball past cover and wide enough of the fielder at mid off for a single
short of a length outside off, defended on the back foot
Bresnan jumps on to the back foot and dabs the ball towards third man
Morgan drives the ball firmly towards cover but can't beat the infield
nudged towards fine leg for one
short of a length outside off, Bresnan stays in his crease and defends towards point
Johnson slants the ball across the right-hander and beats the outside edge of Bresnan's defence
smashed! Morgan plants his front foot forward and swings his bat hard, smacking the ball high over long on, that's the second six of the innings
played towards third man for one
Hopes bowls a slower short ball and Bresnan pulls behind square
good length just outside off, defended on the front foot
nudged off the back foot towards midwicket
full ball on off stump, driven off the front foot towards long-off
played towards mid-off, dot ball
slower ball on middle stump, Morgan sees it and turns it off his pads towards midwicket
Bresnan moves forward and plays the ball to cover
short ball but it's wide down leg side, the crowd cheer as the extra is added to England's total
played off the front foot towards point
full ball on the pads and Bresnan clips it fine, very fine actually and the ball speeds to the fine-leg boundary
full length but the line is better, driven towards cover
slow delivery outside off stump, 67mph, cut towards short third man, the keeper is standing up as well
Bracken goes wide of the crease from round the wicket and bowls a slower ball, Bresnan drives through cover
Morgan strides forward and drives a good length ball towards the man on the sweeper boundary, that was another slower ball
full ball on off stump, that was under 70mph as well, driven on the off side
cut off the back foot, more of a thick outside really towards third man
played on the front foot towards cover, super over that
how has that missed?! What a delivery. Good pace, shaping back on Morgan who's cut in half and somehow that misses his off bail

fuller but straighter and punched down the ground. Mid-on takes a tumble and a fumble, and the crowd jeer! Hurrah for mistakes like those. And mid-on now does the same! Tremendous work by everybody, well done
thick outside edge down to third man. Bracken cleans up with heroism
nice and full, and Morgan whacks him to mid-off
another good-length straight delivery which is on-driven to mid-on
angled to third man
outside off and he swings and misses
short of a length and close to his off stump, Bresnan forces it to point off the back foot
full, straight and he digs it out
tries to pull but can't really time it. Still - he does get a single
firmly and crisply driven. But again, it's just for a single. That's fine for Australia, it really is

defensively pushed out to the off side. Bresnan can't make anything of it. Top stuff from Watson but there's been no attempt by either batsman to be inventive, change his lengths, skip down the pitch or step outside leg. All far too easy
fast and straight! Attempted yorker dug out to Watson at mid-on who then shies at the stumps. Good athlete
full again but outside off, and clunked to mid-off
slower ball on his legs! Bresnan gave himself a lot of room but was surprised by the slower ball and made nothing of it
full toss, dug out straight to mid-off. And that's out! The crowd are practically silent, unable to believe just how limp that dismissal was
tickles this slower ball down to fine leg
shorter ball fended to leg
very full but nicely timed off his legs
steps down the pitch and clunks it to long-off
flicked to leg
that's so out. Swung in late on middle stump as Swann played around it, and that's hitting middle stump halfway up
plays and misses outside off
fired in very straight on middle-and-off, and Sidebottom is nearly squared up but manages to defend it
nudged behind square but that's another terrific over from Watson. He's been seriously tight and impressive today
full, straight, and defended by Sidebottom. A prod. Poor old Sidders hasn't got a hope against Lee here
quick! Seriously quick. Bouncer flies through and Sidebottom sways out of the way
fast, wide, left alone. Too quick for Sid
very fast, just outside off, and Sidders defends by digging it out
tries to pull it, and does pull it, but mistimes this scoopy attempt and is lucky he's not caught
driven with a slash down to third man and he steals the strike
slower ball! This really has been a terrific spell by Watson. He's mixed up his pace beautifully yet maintained a consistent line and length
on the pull but misses. England are almost going backwards here
short of a length and nudged to leg, but Sidebottom's about as quick as a one-legged rhino the poor old chap, and Clarke's throw is....just wide from short midwicket! He's furious with himself
smashing shot. Much more like it. Short of a length, he steps outside leg and cuts it hard over backward point for four
it's a little slower and again he steps outside leg, carving him over extra cover for four. Well timed! Really nailed it
got him! No - no-ball. Full toss, very high, and he tries to hook it by it flies to point, but he's been no-balled. A bit of fortune for England
stands tall and smacks him to mid-on
edged wide of Paine and third man cleans up
nice pull, not unlike Des Haynes
Sidebottom's on the pull and he's boshed it powerfully in front of square for four! Well-set, good solid base, and he thwacked it firmly
late swing at 92.6mph which he digs out firmly

very full but dug out. 92.5mph attempted yorker and the crowd are alive at last as England have begun to take the initiative. It's much too late, of course - of course it is! But it's good to see at any rate
down the leg side, off the pads and Paine manages to stop it
flicked to leg
a full toss, carved down to third man
down the leg side - and a wide
worked out to the off side
goes for a tentative back-foot drive and edges it thickly past Paine for four!
on the pull, and he misses
pushed off the back square of the wicket
nicely played by Sidebottom. He's lining these up. Steps outside leg and guides it to deep cover point
ah, that's such a quality slower ball from Johnson. Bresnan didn't have a clue
faster and Bresnan gives Johnson all three stumps to aim at. And somehow, he misses! Paine takes that sharply to his right - that leapt up on him
a one-handed slap out to the off side and this'll be out if the fielder's throw hits...which it doesn't! White, I think it was, at mid-off
whipped through midwicket with a flick of the wrists. Sidebottom's looking increasingly solid out there
steps back and guides to point
Too good. Or rather, Sidebottom's not sure how to handle this straight delivery, and he blocks it off the back foot
a gentle little dab down to third man
stroked out to the off side
straighter ball and skied miles in the air over the bowler's head, but there's no fielder there. Two more to England
short of a length and very well pulled, powerfully even - but Hauritz, the great Ritzy himself, does very well to cut it off from long-on
speared into his legs, Sidebottom tries to lift him for six but long-off holds a clean and comfortable catch at head height

inn2.comm: full and straight from Anderson, Watson moves across and plays the ball behind square leg
wayward delivery, wide down leg side, Anderson will have to redo that one
too straight once again and Paine gets off the mark with a flick off the pads
good length outside off stump, left alone by Watson
short of a length delivery around off, Watson moves back and defends with a straight bat
blocked once again off the back foot towards cover
relatively tidy start by Anderson, he's on target with the final ball and Watson defends back to the bowler
very very wide, a real loosen-er and that will be one more to Australia
that's wide as well, but not as wide as the previous one, Paine lets it go and this time it's a dot ball
this is closer to Paine that the previous one, he lets it go again
bat on ball for the first time this over, Paine moves back and taps a good length delivery towards point
short of a length outside off, left alone by Paine once again
better length and line just outside off, Paine practices his leave again
what's he trying? Paine moves across to whip a ball from off through leg, he misses and it lobs up on the off side
super delivery from Jimmy, pitches short of a length and seams away from Watson who fends and misses
Watson gets behind the line of a good length ball and defends towards the bowler
full ball on middle and Watson flicks firmly but straight to the man at midwicket
Anderson angles the ball in towards off stump, Watson strides forward and defends
well done Bopara! He dives at square leg and cuts off a firm flick from Watson
nicely placed! Watson moves back and eases the ball on the up through a small gap at cover point
cut off the back foot towards point
tight line and length around middle, defended back to the bowler
Watson tries to dab towards third man but it's too close to his body and the bottom edge bounces to slip
played towards mid-on for no run, slow start this, sluggish pitch as well
Watson moves forward, gets behind the line and defends
Watson waits in his crease and dabs the ball past point for one
Watson moves back and frees his arms to cut the ball through the gap at cover point, it won't reach the boundary and Paine runs back for the third
defended on the leg side
was that intentional? Risky shot if it was ... Paine edged the ball and got it wide of the fielder at first slip
Paine moves across his crease and tries to whip the ball on the leg side, like Pietersen -  Andrew McGlashan says, but not quite as effective
Watson's defence is solid as ever
lbw! Plumb! Anderson seams the ball into Watson, who is caught on the crease, and it hits pad first before going on to bat, that's hit him dead centre and England have their early wicket
wide outside off stump, left alone by the batsman
short of a length on off stump, defended off the back foot on the off side
driven off the front foot towards cover point, Paine can't find the gap
Paine opens the face yet again but can't find a way past point
Paine jumps back and blocks once again
Paine flicks off his pads, it's in the air but falls safely in the gap
Paine strides forward and defends, solidly, on the off side
slightly shorter and slightly wider, Paine plays the ball towards point
this time Paine waits and dabs the ball to third man
Anderson pitches full outside off stump, White, who hasn't played a delivery before this one, lets it go tamely through to the wicketkeeper
short of a length on off stump, White goes back and across to defend
Anderson strays on to leg and White gets going with a flick off his pads, there's a fielder at deep square leg though and he prevents the four
good length ball outside off, left alone by White
played off the back foot towards point
England are keeping Australia quiet, White defends to the off side again
that's hit him where it hurts really really badly, White tried to whip across the line and missed, he went down immediately and is in some pain
Sidebottom's appealing for something but I'm not sure what. It looked like it cut White in half and missed both bat and pad. It bounced before the wicketkeeper as well
defended on the back foot towards the off side
flicked in the air towards mid-on, it doesn't carry but the fielder dives over it and concedes runs
defended, blocked, played carefully
White gets behind the line and defends another, Australia are going at less than three runs an over
White plays another dot ball towards the off side, no run ... just one boundary so far and that was from a dodgy half-edge, half-steer by Paine
White thumps the ball hard at Swann who is at short cover and the ball thuds into his left leg
another dot ball played out on the off side
good length on leg and middle, Paine nudges towards midwicket
White tries to drive down the ground but gets an inside edge through midwicket
Paine stays in his crease and drives on the up towards point
nice shot! Paine jumps down the track and though he isn't to the pitch, he manages to punch it firmly past mid-off for four
worked off the pads between midwicket and mid-on
White drives towards mid-off, no run, that's the end of the first Powerplay
a touch too straight and he whips it to fine leg. Neat turn of the wrists
thwacked down to third man - Bresnan has a really good arm as they come back for two, but they're safely home
down the leg side and he flicks it just wide of the keeper! Anderson gives him an earful. He's a grump beggar these days is Jimmy
pushed out to the off side
short of a length and a good line, too, angling back in on the off stump
very straight, and firmly worked to mid-on, but he can't get it either side of him
flipped off his pads
short of a length and he pushes it out to the off side
and that's not cheered Sidebottom one iota but it's a useful shot to a misdirected bouncer, down the leg side, which is hooked very fine by Paine for four

nice looking drive, though he hasn't quite timed that as well as he might've - nevertheless he gets four as Swann's dive is, well, not the most elegant. "He looks like he's been shot," Nasser Hussain describes it on Sky's commentary, and that's pretty spot on! Like a really rubbish belly flop into a swimming pool
better line this time, forcing the defensive
ooh that's a cracker! Moves a touch away from Paine who stepped outside leg and tried to waft it but missed entirely
angling into the right hander from wide of the crease, and he defends on the back foot
glorious-looking cover drive but straight to the fielder. Full of length from Bresnan
crabs forward and squeezes it out to cover
top shot! He stepped back and flayed it with extravagance, a free-flowing swing of the bat behind square for four. Proper one-day shot
comes forward and is beaten! Tries to jab down on it but played down the wrong line
crunched on the back foot to cover
pumped to mid-on
short of a length and easily whipped to midwicket
got him! A little dibbly dobbly, off-cutting stodger, and it kept horrifically low to trap him in front of middle-and-off. No doubt about that
another off-cutter pushed back to Collingwood and his golden arm
stroked out to cover
and it's defended on the back foot to end a successful first over for Collingwood
on the back foot, he defends
oh well bowled, that hurried him a touch but he nevertheless managed to jab down on it and nudge it to leg
that's done him! Cut back sharply and missed his inside edge
very, very good line to Clarke. Just outside off and Clarke is right behind it, defending solidly
down the leg side and rightly wided
wide of the crease and that's good from Clarke, dropping it to leg and scampering a single
smacked to mid-on and he'll have to hurry! This is perilously close if it hits ... but it's just wide! In fact he'd have been gone by a metre or more...
on the off stump, whipped to short midwicket
well he's lifted this just over midwicket but hasn't timed it
that's 60.5mph! Other things happened, but I'm still reeling from seeing how slow that was
lofted over the top and that's landed like a rock. Thud. Dead.
59.7mph outside off. This is fascinating cricket. How slow can Collingwood go? This is comfortably slower than Monty...
oh he's nailed it! Superb cover drive for four. Placed perfectly and he didn't look to hit it too hard
an off-cutter cramps his forcing stroke off the back foot
slower delivery and Clarke, who is looking really under pressure, nudges to leg
good, straight off-cutter and again Clarke can't make anything of it. It's defended
flipped to leg but Clarke screams "nah," or similar, as there's absolutely no chance of a run
blocked off the back foot
defended on the back foot
a 59.7mph demon, so slow that White almost had time to brew a cuppa in between defending it out to the off side
fullish in length and turned to leg
cuts back on the right-hander who times it to long-on
wrong line. Down the leg side and whipped to square leg
pats forward and defends
short of a length and punched to leg
wide of the crease, angling into Clarke who's defending
good line again. Cracked square of the wicket, but it was too close to the off stump and cramped him for room
full, on middle, and timed to leg
defended on the back foot
timed off his pads to leg and he'll get a single this time
shapes back into him and it's again defended, and Bresnan receives some flesh-slapping in congratulations from his team-mates
defended on the back foot
turned to leg
biff, bash, bosh! Thudding shot over the top, over long-off
full of length and flicked to leg
oh well bowled, almost squaring him up, but the batsman does really well to wait for it - waiting, waiting, waiting before squeezing it back past the bowler
down the leg side and Prior dives to his left, parrying it away. Does well
punched off the back foot
good length and straight, Clarke works the ball off his pads
Bresnan angles the ball into the pads, White plays it towards midwicket
forced off the back foot through cover
short of a length on off and middle, defended back to the bowler
Wait! yells Clarke after playing the ball to mid-on
Clarke takes a step towards the off side and works the ball through square leg
full ball on off and middle, driven back to the bowler
bangs it in short of a length, angling into Clarke, who plays towards point and runs the single
width offered outside off stump and White chases it but misses, Wright got it to move a shade away from the right-hander
punched off the back foot towards cover
pushed off the back foot towards the leg side
White goes back to defend a good length ball and gets a thick outside edge towards third man
cut hard into the ground and over point for one
Clarke moves across and towards the ball before driving to cover
short ball and Clarke swivels but misses the pull
Clarke gets behind the line of one and blocks towards the bowler
Clarke's found the gap in the infield with the square drive, but that's because the fielder at point went deep for the last two balls of the over
another quick single to end the over
full and straight from Wright, White defends on the front foot
defended on the front foot towards cover
White tries to flick on the leg but misses, the batsmen run a leg bye anyway
tapped towards cover, they think about a run but decide against it, wisely
Clarke drives the ball past point for a single
good length on off, White stays in his crease and plays the ball on the off side
that was 55 mph ... Clarke cuts off the back foot through cover point
White lunges forward and defends but gets hit on the pad outside the line of off stump
quicker one that time and White plays off his pads through square leg
slog swept and slog swept into the space on the deep backward square leg boundary, powerful shot and well placed
nudged on the leg side for a quick single
Clarke comes down the track but doesn't get to the pitch of the ball
driven firmly towards backward point where Collingwood swoops to his left and saves runs, fine effort from the acting captain!
defended on the back foot towards the off
Wright's keeping it tight around off and middle, White defends on the back foot towards point
White moves across his stumps and nudges the ball behind square
short of a length with a hint of seam away from the right-hander, Clarke fends and misses
Clarke jumps across his crease and flicks towards deep backward square, fine over from Wright, very economical
played behind point on the off side and Clarke is quick to return for the second
Clarke skips down the track and plays the ball to midwicket
on the front foot, he comes forward to defend
down the pitch with half a shuffle, and he gets an outside edge down to Anderson at third man
touch too short and pumped to long-on
very full - too full to cut, but that's what he attempted and got a thick inside edge
good line, he's back and defending. Excellent control from Wright
on the back foot and he nudges it defensively to the leg side
very good length, if a touch too wide of the off stump, but nevertheless he doesn't concede a run. Forced to mid-off
short of a length, guided to point and Clarke roars his anger at yet again not grabbing a single
good length on off stump, played off the front foot behind point
Collingwood bowls a cutter on off stump, Clarke moves back and plays to short third man
Clarke tries to pull a very short ball but is just too early on the shot, he doesn't make proper contact
played back to the bowler on the front foot
played off the front foot towards mid-on
another single to end the over, Australia are doing this with confidence now
White works the ball off his pads towards midwicket
White strides forward and drives through cover
played off the front foot towards mid-off

that would have been run out my miles and miles! White nudged the ball towards mid-on and set off, Anderson intercepted from midwicket and under-armed the ball at the stumps with White not in the frame, he could have taken a few more steps and done a Jonty
another quick single and this time the throw from mid-on goes to the wicketkeeper, the batsmen are safe this time though
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
forced out to the off side
incredibly slow! 58mph off-cutter which really troubled the right-hander who went forward, then nudged to leg
and he's squared him up slightly here, angling it into the right-hander who pushed it back with an angled bat
on the pull for a single
a little bit too short and he pumps it off the back foot to long-on. Well timed
too short and whipped to leg - but very well stopped by short midwicket. Excellent work there
flighted outside the off stump, and he comes forward to flick it to leg
too short, and he picks up his fifty with a whip off his hip
cracked to long-off
worked on the leg side
oh that's a horror from Swann but he escapes punishment, as this crunching back-foot smack finds cover
cracked down the ground to long-on
straighter and a touch quicker from Collingwood, but he's quick on the front foot and flips it to leg for a quick single
good footwork. Onto the front foot, driving out to mid-off - very quick to come forward
down the leg side but that's a bit of a harsh call by the umpire
on the back foot, nice and full and he punches it back to the bowler
tossed up fuller and driven out to long-on

pulled and skied - that's gone miles up in the air and appeared to be heading for six, but Sidebottom scurries around from fine leg to field. Collingwood's not happy about his effort; perhaps he didn't pick it up quickly enough
beautifully back-cut! There a shot for the purists, of whom I am a paid-up member. Nothing better than a delicate late-cut
down the pitch and Clarke tries to hustle this over cover, as he threw his hands at it and tried to force it but couldn't time it
down the pitch and tried to whack it over point but it falls short! Well bowled by Swann
down the leg side
on the back foot, punched off the back foot
oh brilliant shot, well played - he gave himself room, and lofted it over extra cover. That's the flexibility of White, able to change his speed
slashed wide of third man for three more
defended out to the off side
quicker, fuller and straighter and it's worked to leg
chopped to point. "Wait on," is the cry from Clarke and a reasonable one, too, as Collingwood doth lurk at point
flicked off his pads nicely for a jogged single
on the back foot, it's elegantly forced square of the wicket
angled down to third man
and he begins nicely with one on the middle stump which Clarke defends furiously
good, tight line once more just outside the off stump this time, and Clarke's quick to rock back and defend it with composure out to the off side
another defensive on the back foot
touch wide of the off stump but again Clarke can't break the gap at cover
glided out to the off side for a single, at last
well bowled Sidebottom. Just the single from it, and Australia's target is pretty much a run-a-ball
short, pulled with power to midwicket
flayed down to third man - nearly for four, but Swann did well to scamper round and make a good pick-up-and-return in one fluid motion. Well, as fluid as Graeme ever is in the field
ever so slightly shorter this time, inviting White to dab it fine once more but he finds backward point
flogged through midwicket! Absolutely flogged. No style or beauty about that stroke, he just waited for one to angle into him, stepped down the pitch and wellied it on the front foot for four
nice comeback from Bresnan, dropping that in pace by some distance. It's given respect from White
again, nicely bowled. Nudged to leg
sheesh he timed that! Clarke smiles - he really hit it beautifully and shakes his head at the irony. When it's not going your way, there's very little you can do about it. Cover cleans up
forced to cover
clipped off his pads to short midwicket
crisply forced through cover this time - he's broken through the covers! Rejoice! But not enough for four
tries to work it to leg but it comes off his pads
drives to long-off and steals the strike
Clarke defends with the straightest of blades
ooh that's hit him on the glove I think and squared him up, out to the off side. Bounced up a touch more than he thought and Clarke stares questionably at his bat
comes forward, driving out to mid-off

flicked to leg and they go for a single - disaster, there's a mix-up! But the throw is a pathetic, meek, half-cocked, lazy, back-of-the-hand flick and Anderson's in front of the stumps and can't collect it. What a total and utter shambles
forced off the back foot
defended off the back foot once more to end a good over
starts well with one on middle-and-leg, turned to mid-on
slapped to cover on the front foot. Nailed it. But straight to cover
flogged! Flogged for six over midwicket. The long levers came out and he swatted it from outside off, over midwicket, for a towering six. Bang!
flayed over extra cover this time. White's pumped up and ready to rumble
short of a length and slapped to deep extra cover
flicked to short fine-leg, Shah, the Middlesex legend, wings in a good throw
White dabs the ball on the offside, the ball pitches close to the stumps and spins back towards the leg side, they run a single
driven off the pads towards long on for a single
played with soft hands towards the off side, quick single taken
pushed towards cover, another quick single
Anderson drifts on to leg and the batsman uses the angle to flick towards deep square
full toss on middle stump, White works it through midwicket, seven from the over
full ball outside off, White winds up and unfurls a powerful drive that beats the infield but gets cut off on the boundary
White stays on the back foot and dabs the ball towards short third man for a single
Clarke makes room by moving towards leg and plays a pleasing drive towards long off
a low full toss outside off, White hits it straight to cover, Clarke sets off but gets sent back, he has to hurry but the throw misses, it was way off target
in the block hole outside off stump, White tries to chop it down to third man but doesn't make contact
another one in the block hole, the line is straighter though and White digs it out towards long-on, the fielder rushes in but doesn't pick up cleanly and allows the second
Clarke's standing a long way outside leg by the time the ball reaches him, he flicks towards deep square, he's standing so far outside leg to give himself room to hit on the off
Anderson bowls a straight one and goes between Clarke and the stumps, well bowled
normal stance this time for Clarke and he works the ball through square leg
Anderson strays down leg and White moves into the nineties with a deft nudge to the fine-leg boundary

Dropped! Bresnan has grassed an absolute sitter! White was foxed by the slower ball and was way too early on the drive, he lofted the ball high in the air to long-on for the simplest of catches, Bresnan simply clanged it
a single to end the over, ten runs from it
White makes room, waits for the ball, and lofts inside out into the huge vacant spaces on the cover boundary, that's four and White's on 99

White reaches hundred by nudging the ball towards the leg side, he gets a cheer from the crowd and a hug from Clarke, his captain hasn't been in the most fluent form and White's taken the responsibility of leading Australia to victory, fine innings

the mid-on is in the circle and Clarke charges Swann and lofts over the fielder for four, that's his first boundary and it brings up his half-century, it's been tough going for Clarke but he's hung in there

he's not hanging on anymore! Clarke charges again and has a swing at the ball, Swann beats him in flight and turns the ball past the bat and on to the stumps, it's perhaps too little too late for England though
worked off the pads towards midwicket, eight fielders in the circle for Ferguson
nudged off the pads towards short fine leg, no run, the batting Powerplay is done with
full toss and White flicks to deep square leg, confident shot
Ferguson gets off the mark by playing to point and sprinting as if his life depended on it
driven down to long on for one more
Bresnan strays on to leg stump and Ferguson helps the ball on its way to the fine leg boundary, poor delivery, Bresnan hasn't had the best ten minutes of his life
played off the back foot towards cover
short and wide, the batsman reaches out for it and cuts wide of the fielder at third man, Australia move two runs closer to a 3-0 lead
Ferguson stays still in his crease and then, with minimal fuss, flicks the ball behind square
full toss and White forces it through square leg for one more
the slower short ball and Ferguson misses the pull, Prior fumbles though and the batsmen steal a bye
full and straight from Wright, but White moves forward and drives towards cover point
nudged off the pads for one more
full toss and it gets driven straight past the bowler for one
wide ball outside off stump, poor stuff from Bresnan and Ferguson cashes in, he frees his arms and cuts the ball through the gap at cover point
there's an appeal for lbw but it's missing leg stump, the batsmen run a leg bye
Bresnan digs it in short but it's slanting down leg side, no wide called though
sliding down leg again and White flicks firmly towards deep midwicket
Ferguson latches on to the width outside off and cuts hard behind point for another four
played off the back foot towards mid-on, Australia can afford dot balls now
wide outside off stump, White throws his bat at it but doesn't make contact

caught! White flat-bats another short and wide ball straight to Sidebottom at mid-off, it was the slower one from Wright and White connected with the bottom of the bat, well played White, his century's taken Australia to the verge of a 3-0 lead
played off the back foot on the off side, dot ball ... 9 from 15 balls
massive appeal for lbw after Wright cuts the ball back into Ferguson and hits the pad, that was a touch too high
played back to the bowler, another dot ball ... good stuff from Wright
Hussey plays and misses, he was no where close to making contact
Ferguson jumps down the track and dabs to the off side, the batsmen hesitate but then decide to take on the fielder, Bopara misses at the bowler's end with Ferguson at least a foot short

Hussey jumps down the track and chips the ball high in the air over wide mid-on, there's no one there and the ball bounces and rolls slowly towards the boundary, it doesn't get there but the batsmen run four!
that's it, it's all over, Hussey plays a half-pull, half-hook to the boundary ... Australia take a 3-0 lead and they won this game at a canter
